As shown in [*How to Use Scroll Panes: Providing Custom Decorations*][1], you can use the scroll pane&#39;s `setCorner()` method to add a colored `Component`:

    JPanel panel = new JPanel();
    panel.setBackground(Color.gray);
    scrollPane.setCorner(JScrollPane.UPPER_RIGHT_CORNER, panel);

You may have to set the panel&#39;s [opacity][2] to `true`, and you may want to select a suitable color from the the current Look &amp; Feel using the [`UIManager`][3].


  [1]: http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/uiswing/components/scrollpane.html#decorations
  [2]: http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/painting-140037.html#props
  [3]: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.desktop/javax/swing/UIManager.html

